"Isabelle G.-M.","Energy-related logics of action throughout the ages in France: Historical milestones, stages of life and intergenerational transmissions",2011,"Energy Efficiency","4","4",,"493","509",,,10.1007/s12053-011-9124-8,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-80052551125&partnerID=40&md5=9e52f867aec3486ccb8ed29cf32cb1ee","EDF R and D (Electricité de France, Research and Development), 1 avenue du Général de Gaulle, 92141 Clamart, France","Isabelle, G.-M., EDF R and D (Electricité de France, Research and Development), 1 avenue du Général de Gaulle, 92141 Clamart, France","Energy use is a very important question nowadays in the context of global warming and the cost of energy. ""Energy conservation"" is paradoxal: environmental awareness is increasing, but so is energy demand. Sociological knowledge concerning energy uses and energy savings remain important to understand the possible evolution of practices and values and thus possible future energy policies. Can the ""consumer society"" become a ""less energy-intensive"" society? This paper's purpose was to understand how individuals, at each stage of life, in the context of historic events and intra-familial relationships, build a specific relationship to energy and ""energy care"" (paying attention to energy) and a specific appropriation of public policies, energy-efficient technologies and environmental discourses. The notion of ""logics of action"" provides a way to combine the analysis of historical events and the analysis of daily practices, integrating the way people act, the justification of actions and the dynamics of life course stages. The social age approach has policy implications, for example, helping to segment people's profiles and to tailor the tools to age groups. The paper also questions the fact that some policies focus on children to transmit their messages. This paper is based on the analysis of several qualitative studies in various age groups of French people. © 2011 Springer Science+Business Media B.V.","Anthropology; Behaviour; Familial transmissions; France; Generations; Practices","Anthropology; Behaviour; Familial transmissions; France; Generations; Practices; Energy management; Energy policy; Global warming; Public policy; Quality control; Energy efficiency; action plan; energy conservation; energy efficiency; energy policy; energy use; global warming; social behavior; France",,,,,,"(2009) Les ménages apprivoisent la maîtrise de l'énergie à la maison, (17). , ADEME & Vous, ADEME Stratégie et études; Attias-Donfut, C., (1988) Sociologie Des générations. L'empreinte Du Temps, , Paris: PUF; Bégué, M.-C., La maîtrise de la demande en électricité en France, entre impératif environnemental et hésitations politiques (2005) Annales historiques de l'électricité, (3), pp. 49-61. , EDF Fondation/Victoires Editions; Berger, P.L., Luckmann, T., (1966) The Social Construction of Reality: A Treatise in the Sociology of Knowledge, , Garden City: Anchor Books; Bertoldi, P., Atanasiu, B., (2007) Electricity consumption and efficiency trends in the enlarged European Union, , Report JRC/IES EUR 22753EN; Bourdieu, P., (1984) Question De Sociologie, , Paris: Les Editions de Minuit; Caradec, V., (2001) Sociologie De La Vieillesse Et Du Vieillissement, , Paris: Nathan; Darby, S., Social learning and public policy: lessons from an energy-conscious village (2006) Energy Policy, 34, pp. 2929-2940; de Singly, F., (2006) Les Adonaissants, , Paris: Armand Colin; Desjeux, D., Berthier, C., Jarraffoux, S., Orhant, I., Taponier, S., (1996) Anthropologie De L'électricité. Les Objets électriques Dans La Vie Quotidienne En France, , Paris: L'Harmattan; Dobré, M., (2002) L'écologie Au Quotidien: Eléments Pour Une théorie Sociologique De La résistance Ordinaire, , Paris: L'Harmattan; Dobré, M., Société de consommation et risque environnemental (2003) Dictionnaire Des Risques, pp. 79-86. , Y. Dupont (Ed.), Paris: Armand Colin; Filliastre, M., (2008) Les Adolescents é